#
# Safe configuration (use arity-specific templates):
#   VPN_SWITCH_INTERPRETER_wireguard_add1=sh
#   VPN_SWITCH_INTERPRETER_wireguard_add2=<combinator-interpreter>
#   VPN_SWITCH_INTERPRETER_wireguard_add3=sh
#
# Or simply rely on defaults:
#   - add1 and add3 use VPN_SWITCH_TERMINAL_INTERPRETER (defaults to 'cat', set to 'sh' for auto-exec)
#   - add2 uses VPN_SWITCH_COMBINATOR_INTERPRETER (correct combinator execution)
#
# Default value: "cat" (SAFE - display only, no execution)
#   This prevents accidental breakage if family interpreter is mistakenly set
#   All add commands will display output without executing
